<p>And I'm not assuming anything. I only brought up 1811 because of the severity. A little research shows that the first recorded earthquake in the area was felt by a French explorer in the 1600s. Geologic evidence shows a long history of activity. USGS says at least 35 shocks of intensity V (Mercalli Modified) or greater have been recorded in Missouri since 1811. Since the geology exists and our tweaking seems to be making it worse, I don't think it's an unreasonable thing to insure against.</p>

